reviewText:
Early Access Review

I really like the concept of the game - it's really something refreshing so let's hope devs won't suddenly dissappear with our money lol;D

Pro:
-World is really intresting to explore, it lives its own life - impressive to see how settlement is build where was nothing;
-level up system is Gothic like (find your teacher) so that's cool;
-Building system is quite intresting as well as craft;

Contra:
-AI system needs to be developed much-much more - more quests and AI behvoir algorithms;
-Optimization could be better (i have 970Gt and lags after about an hour of play - need restart to fix it)

Hm.. This game needs to be developed, and if developers will make what they'll promise i'll play this game for hours, so YES" for now."

Early Access Review

Hi, that's my first review so don't be too angry with that:)
+Potential - game is only EA, as far as i know it's updated, so things are good in this direction;
+Intresting idea - random everything;
+Living world - game really liuves its own life - cities are build, people are doing something all the time - the world is procedural btw - so devs. its a good job, really!
+Bow combat is ok for me - arrows hasphysics, you have to think before shootong;
+building system - is alos quite intresting depending on you perks (might be better actually), hope devs will make it better in future updates;

-performance - after some time of play (1,5 hours) lags appear - i know, that's EA but i wish those lags won't be there;
-close combat - need to be developed;
-sometimes AI just snatds and waiting for something - is it ok?

Sum: Well, if the price of 9.99 won't change and the devs will do everything they're promising us in the roadmap - this game will be one of my favorotes ones, so i recommend to buy it:)

Ps. Just found a cave in the ruins!
